1
00:00:26,160 --> 00:00:29,570
♪Peach blossoms fall,
yesterday's trace fades away♪

2
00:00:29,790 --> 00:00:33,070
♪Ahead lie storms and winds,
our fates like drifting clouds sway♪

3
00:00:33,380 --> 00:00:39,030
♪Alas, I roam through what remains,
fate's grip won't set me free♪

4
00:00:40,380 --> 00:00:43,920
♪If time would spare me
just one breath to stay♪

5
00:00:44,530 --> 00:00:47,920
♪If you could see
the depth of my belief♪

6
00:00:48,120 --> 00:00:54,680
♪Alone I enter the game,
every move made with no regret in me♪

7
00:00:55,060 --> 00:00:59,050
♪Though shackles bind my soul
and chain my form♪

8
00:00:59,160 --> 00:01:02,320
♪I've walked
through life and death before♪

9
00:01:02,320 --> 00:01:09,190
♪I fear not fate's cruel temptations,
I've severed every cause♪

10
00:01:09,410 --> 00:01:13,430
♪In this life our threads entwined,
in love and pain we crossed♪

11
00:01:13,600 --> 00:01:16,560
♪But I'll keep my word
no matter the cost♪

12
00:01:16,560 --> 00:01:19,030
♪Forged in stardust and flame♪

13
00:01:19,030 --> 00:01:24,790
♪I rise with an unyielding frame♪

14
00:01:34,100 --> 00:01:36,038
=The Princess's Gambit=

15
00:01:36,040 --> 00:01:38,510
(Adapted from the novel "Peach Blossoms
Reflecting the River and Mountains")

16
00:01:38,511 --> 00:01:40,980
(by Bai Lu Cheng Shuang)

17
00:01:41,140 --> 00:01:43,900
=Episode 9=

18
00:02:23,280 --> 00:02:24,640
Am I seeing things?

19
00:02:25,640 --> 00:02:27,840
Why did I see the treacherous chancellor
chopping wood?

20
00:02:32,680 --> 00:02:34,840
Sir is such a good man.

21
00:02:35,840 --> 00:02:37,640
I'm old and useless.

22
00:02:37,920 --> 00:02:39,520
Lian is frail.

23
00:02:40,080 --> 00:02:41,840
The firewood in the woodshed

24
00:02:41,960 --> 00:02:43,480
is all branches picked up from outside.

25
00:02:43,840 --> 00:02:44,640
Sir saw it

26
00:02:44,680 --> 00:02:46,440
and chopped some wood
early in the morning.

27
00:02:47,520 --> 00:02:48,360
He hasn't

28
00:02:49,080 --> 00:02:50,280
rested at all.

29
00:02:54,520 --> 00:02:56,440
Sir asked me to get a sweat towel.

30
00:02:57,080 --> 00:02:58,080
Since you're here,

31
00:02:58,440 --> 00:02:59,960
you can wipe his sweat.

32
00:03:01,760 --> 00:03:02,280
Go.

33
00:03:05,640 --> 00:03:06,720
(What?)

34
00:03:07,640 --> 00:03:09,120
(I have to wipe his sweat?)

35
00:03:35,040 --> 00:03:35,360
No need.

36
00:03:36,200 --> 00:03:36,960
I can do it myself.

37
00:03:37,280 --> 00:03:38,000
Alright.

38
00:03:39,080 --> 00:03:39,880
Come here.

39
00:03:40,120 --> 00:03:41,440
Come and eat.

40
00:03:41,760 --> 00:03:42,280
Coming.

41
00:03:50,320 --> 00:03:50,840
Granny.

42
00:03:51,640 --> 00:03:53,120
We walked around the village yesterday

43
00:03:53,440 --> 00:03:55,240
and really like the countryside.

44
00:03:55,700 --> 00:03:57,400
I wonder if we can stay
for a few more days

45
00:03:57,760 --> 00:03:58,760
and inquire

46
00:03:58,800 --> 00:03:59,840
about carriages to Yujing.

47
00:04:00,520 --> 00:04:01,560
That won't work.

48
00:04:01,720 --> 00:04:03,200
You agreed to stay for only one day.

49
00:04:04,520 --> 00:04:05,480
It's not a big deal.

50
00:04:06,360 --> 00:04:07,280
If you like it,

51
00:04:07,600 --> 00:04:08,720
just stay.

52
00:04:10,120 --> 00:04:11,720
Ask Lian to help with the carriage.

53
00:04:12,640 --> 00:04:14,520
She's always running around.

54
00:04:14,800 --> 00:04:15,240
I refuse.

55
00:04:17,000 --> 00:04:17,280
You...

56
00:04:17,560 --> 00:04:18,360
Where are you going?

57
00:04:19,760 --> 00:04:22,240
Sorry, this child has a temper.

58
00:04:22,480 --> 00:04:23,000
It's alright.

59
00:04:23,440 --> 00:04:23,920
Don't worry.

60
00:04:24,240 --> 00:04:25,120
During our stay here,

61
00:04:25,480 --> 00:04:26,400
we'll handle

62
00:04:26,640 --> 00:04:27,480
the farm work.

63
00:04:50,880 --> 00:04:51,320
Sir.

64
00:04:52,040 --> 00:04:52,880
Take a break.

65
00:04:53,080 --> 00:04:53,760
Drink some water.

66
00:04:54,760 --> 00:04:55,080
Alright.

67
00:05:02,560 --> 00:05:04,080
You agreed to leave in a day!

68
00:05:04,440 --> 00:05:05,480
You didn't keep your word!

69
00:05:07,120 --> 00:05:09,400
It's you for being too gullible.

70
00:05:10,800 --> 00:05:12,080
I'll keep an eye on you

71
00:05:12,200 --> 00:05:13,480
and see what you're up to!

72
00:05:15,040 --> 00:05:15,400
Sit down.

73
00:05:15,680 --> 00:05:15,960
Sure.

74
00:05:22,360 --> 00:05:23,520
You worked all morning.

75
00:05:23,880 --> 00:05:24,520
Have some water.

76
00:05:27,320 --> 00:05:27,560
Here.

77
00:05:28,040 --> 00:05:28,440
Thank you.

78
00:05:42,240 --> 00:05:43,880
This village is poor,

79
00:05:44,420 --> 00:05:46,400
but the villagers
live in peace and contentment.

80
00:05:48,600 --> 00:05:49,840
If I could settle down here

81
00:05:50,560 --> 00:05:51,920
and stay away from court disputes,

82
00:05:52,720 --> 00:05:53,640
wouldn't that be great?

83
00:05:57,480 --> 00:05:58,960
The countryside is soothing,

84
00:06:00,600 --> 00:06:01,760
but not everyone is qualified

85
00:06:01,760 --> 00:06:03,040
to stay away from court disputes

86
00:06:03,840 --> 00:06:04,880
and live freely.

87
00:06:07,620 --> 00:06:09,520
You've been in a high position
for a long time.

88
00:06:10,240 --> 00:06:11,840
Many things must be beyond your control,

89
00:06:13,240 --> 00:06:14,080
but sometimes

90
00:06:14,520 --> 00:06:15,600
holding on to a yearning

91
00:06:16,000 --> 00:06:17,440
is to preserve a small patch of peace

92
00:06:18,480 --> 00:06:19,760
within one's heart.

93
00:06:21,720 --> 00:06:22,440
What do you think?

94
00:06:24,080 --> 00:06:25,080
(This yearning)

95
00:06:25,440 --> 00:06:26,240
(doesn't seem fake.)

96
00:06:27,800 --> 00:06:28,320
(Maybe)

97
00:06:29,480 --> 00:06:31,440
(you're also acting against your heart.)

98
00:06:39,600 --> 00:06:40,600
(Jiang Taohua.)

99
00:06:41,200 --> 00:06:42,600
(If you weren't Beiyuan's princess,)

100
00:06:43,640 --> 00:06:44,640
(wouldn't that be great?)

101
00:07:15,600 --> 00:07:16,280
Miss.

102
00:07:16,360 --> 00:07:17,800
I don't mean to give you a hard time.

103
00:07:18,080 --> 00:07:19,640
It's just that Chancellor isn't around.

104
00:07:19,640 --> 00:07:20,440
No one is in charge.

105
00:07:20,680 --> 00:07:22,120
Go back to your room and rest.

106
00:07:22,920 --> 00:07:23,760
Zaiye isn't around.

107
00:07:24,040 --> 00:07:25,080
Meng Zhenzhen can't decide.

108
00:07:25,120 --> 00:07:26,240
And you're making excuses.

109
00:07:26,320 --> 00:07:27,480
Are you trying to drive me mad

110
00:07:27,480 --> 00:07:29,040
from being cooped up in this residence?

111
00:07:29,040 --> 00:07:29,560
I don't care.

112
00:07:29,760 --> 00:07:31,240
If you don't give me an answer today,

113
00:07:31,240 --> 00:07:32,520
you can forget about going out.

114
00:07:39,880 --> 00:07:40,200
Alright.

115
00:07:40,520 --> 00:07:41,240
I'm not going out.

116
00:07:45,520 --> 00:07:46,240
What do you mean?

117
00:07:47,040 --> 00:07:48,000
Sorry for offending you.

118
00:07:48,440 --> 00:07:49,720
But it concerns your safety.

119
00:07:49,800 --> 00:07:50,720
I have no other choice.

120
00:07:51,000 --> 00:07:52,040
Take Miss back to her room.

121
00:07:52,040 --> 00:07:53,920
Please take good care of her
during this period.

122
00:07:53,920 --> 00:07:54,490
- Yes.
- Yes.

123
00:07:54,600 --> 00:07:55,280
No!

124
00:07:55,640 --> 00:07:56,160
Zhan Lu!

125
00:07:56,600 --> 00:07:57,160
Zhan Lu!

126
00:07:57,560 --> 00:07:59,160
I'm going to tell Zaiye about you!

127
00:08:03,840 --> 00:08:04,880
(How dare you, Zhan Lu?)

128
00:08:05,200 --> 00:08:06,240
(You won't let me go out,)

129
00:08:06,520 --> 00:08:07,720
(yet you go out quite often.)

130
00:08:09,720 --> 00:08:12,000
(But why did he go out
if Zaiye isn't around?)

131
00:08:12,440 --> 00:08:13,680
(Did something happen to Zaiye?)

132
00:08:34,700 --> 00:08:36,360
(Half of Sunlight over a Thousand Peaks.)

133
00:08:37,480 --> 00:08:39,040
(Who are you going to give the rest to?)

134
00:08:40,300 --> 00:08:42,120
(It seems
that you never really believed me.)

135
00:08:43,120 --> 00:08:44,080
(The so-called alliance)

136
00:08:44,920 --> 00:08:46,480
(is just a cover for you to survive.)

137
00:08:52,480 --> 00:08:54,180
Why are you peeling
so many bamboo shoots?

138
00:08:54,760 --> 00:08:56,040
My husband worked hard today.

139
00:08:56,640 --> 00:08:58,320
I want to stew
some bamboo shoots for him.

140
00:08:59,160 --> 00:09:00,480
But this is too much.

141
00:09:00,840 --> 00:09:01,560
It doesn't matter.

142
00:09:02,480 --> 00:09:03,280
My husband loves it.

143
00:09:10,840 --> 00:09:12,080
(She's full of schemes)

144
00:09:12,520 --> 00:09:13,560
(and has a hidden agenda,)

145
00:09:14,640 --> 00:09:16,880
(but looked pitiful and loyal.)

146
00:09:19,620 --> 00:09:21,600
(I prided myself
for seeing through many people,)

147
00:09:23,000 --> 00:09:24,480
(yet I was also almost deceived,)

148
00:09:25,360 --> 00:09:27,280
(risking my life to save you.)

149
00:09:28,320 --> 00:09:29,160
(Shen Zaiye.)

150
00:09:29,640 --> 00:09:30,200
(From now on,)

151
00:09:30,760 --> 00:09:32,680
(don't trust this woman.)

152
00:09:41,440 --> 00:09:42,640
Why didn't you get changed?

153
00:09:50,720 --> 00:09:52,720
Sir looks scary.

154
00:09:54,080 --> 00:09:55,080
I agree.

155
00:09:56,480 --> 00:09:57,800
Did you have an argument?

156
00:09:58,160 --> 00:09:59,440
Hurry and coax him.

157
00:10:00,120 --> 00:10:00,680
Me?

158
00:10:01,640 --> 00:10:02,680
I'm a lady.

159
00:10:03,040 --> 00:10:04,560
Why should I coax a grown man?

160
00:10:05,320 --> 00:10:05,880
Miss.

161
00:10:06,100 --> 00:10:08,280
Be careful not to let another woman
steal your husband.

162
00:10:09,200 --> 00:10:11,280
There aren't many men in our village.

163
00:10:11,720 --> 00:10:13,040
Now that one finally showed up,

164
00:10:13,080 --> 00:10:14,280
and such a heroic one at that,

165
00:10:14,640 --> 00:10:16,080
many women have been secretly

166
00:10:16,080 --> 00:10:17,440
asking my grandmother about him.

167
00:10:17,880 --> 00:10:19,040
If you don't want to end up

168
00:10:19,040 --> 00:10:20,240
being alone,

169
00:10:20,480 --> 00:10:21,920
cherish him.

170
00:10:29,880 --> 00:10:31,880
These young ladies are blind.

171
00:10:32,000 --> 00:10:34,140
How could they fall
for such a treacherous chancellor?

172
00:10:38,480 --> 00:10:40,960
Sir is strong and has a great figure!

173
00:10:41,380 --> 00:10:43,640
What does him having a strong figure
have to do with you?

174
00:10:44,480 --> 00:10:45,040
Sir.

175
00:10:45,440 --> 00:10:47,680
Come to our house at noon
to taste our cooking!

176
00:10:48,480 --> 00:10:49,320
I'm not bragging.

177
00:10:49,600 --> 00:10:50,400
My daughter

178
00:10:50,480 --> 00:10:51,880
is a great cook.

179
00:10:52,240 --> 00:10:53,040
Go to my house.

180
00:10:53,320 --> 00:10:54,880
My family killed a chicken today.

181
00:10:56,080 --> 00:10:57,440
Isn't your daughter engaged?

182
00:10:57,440 --> 00:10:58,880
Why are you still having other ideas?

183
00:10:59,040 --> 00:10:59,480
No need.

184
00:10:59,840 --> 00:11:01,320
I just want to be alone for a while.

185
00:11:02,600 --> 00:11:03,680
The word "alone"

186
00:11:03,720 --> 00:11:06,000
sounds melodious when Sir says it.

187
00:11:06,200 --> 00:11:07,040
He must be a scholar.

188
00:11:07,320 --> 00:11:07,880
Sir.

189
00:11:08,160 --> 00:11:09,040
Where do you reside?

190
00:11:09,720 --> 00:11:10,803
You're even asking him that?

191
00:11:10,880 --> 00:11:11,920
Will you quit it?

192
00:11:12,200 --> 00:11:13,720
Sir is already married.

193
00:11:13,880 --> 00:11:15,280
He has a wife.

194
00:11:15,560 --> 00:11:16,080
Darling.

195
00:11:17,840 --> 00:11:18,880
His wife is here.

196
00:11:19,320 --> 00:11:20,320
Hurry, go.

197
00:11:21,840 --> 00:11:22,680
Didn't you invite him

198
00:11:22,760 --> 00:11:24,240
to your house for chicken?

199
00:11:24,720 --> 00:11:25,520
Come eat.

200
00:11:26,160 --> 00:11:27,040
Granny

201
00:11:27,080 --> 00:11:28,880
saw you went out to farm without eating

202
00:11:29,400 --> 00:11:30,200
and asked me

203
00:11:30,320 --> 00:11:31,640
to bring you some food.

204
00:11:48,480 --> 00:11:49,000
Tell me.

205
00:11:49,440 --> 00:11:50,800
As a chancellor,

206
00:11:51,400 --> 00:11:53,320
yet you're more skilled at farming

207
00:11:53,840 --> 00:11:55,360
than actual farmers.

208
00:11:55,800 --> 00:11:57,480
Is it the important matter
you mentioned?

209
00:12:03,720 --> 00:12:04,240
What's wrong?

210
00:12:05,240 --> 00:12:06,760
You're digging into my past.

211
00:12:07,720 --> 00:12:09,160
Are you hoping to find some clue

212
00:12:09,160 --> 00:12:09,880
to use against me?

213
00:12:11,240 --> 00:12:11,720
I advise you

214
00:12:12,480 --> 00:12:13,560
to stop wasting your time.

215
00:12:15,360 --> 00:12:15,880
I'm full.

216
00:12:16,960 --> 00:12:17,840
Remember your mission.

217
00:12:22,240 --> 00:12:23,880
Why is this man so fickle?

218
00:12:24,720 --> 00:12:25,240
Seriously.

219
00:12:28,240 --> 00:12:30,020
(Shen Residence)

220
00:12:47,480 --> 00:12:48,320
Miss Qingying?

221
00:12:52,880 --> 00:12:53,680
What a coincidence.

222
00:12:54,260 --> 00:12:56,480
I practiced lightness skill
at the courtyard wall today,

223
00:12:56,480 --> 00:12:57,680
but there was a minor accident.

224
00:12:58,480 --> 00:13:00,480
Are you here to see Zaiye or Lady Jiang?

225
00:13:00,840 --> 00:13:02,240
Do as you please.

226
00:13:03,320 --> 00:13:04,600
Are you sneaking out?

227
00:13:06,840 --> 00:13:07,240
Yes.

228
00:13:07,440 --> 00:13:08,960
I'm going to find Zaiye and Lady Jiang.

229
00:13:11,480 --> 00:13:12,240
Find Lady Jiang?

230
00:13:14,240 --> 00:13:15,360
Did something happen to her?

231
00:13:15,400 --> 00:13:17,600
Does it have anything to do
with her beating Prince Wugou

232
00:13:17,600 --> 00:13:18,240
on the street?

233
00:13:18,880 --> 00:13:19,760
She beat His Highness?

234
00:13:20,480 --> 00:13:21,000
No wonder.

235
00:13:21,720 --> 00:13:22,880
It's urgent, I won't say more.

236
00:13:23,240 --> 00:13:23,680
Wait.

237
00:13:24,440 --> 00:13:25,120
I'll go with you.

238
00:13:26,880 --> 00:13:27,520
You?

239
00:13:29,680 --> 00:13:32,040
You're delicate and don't know Kung Fu.

240
00:13:32,120 --> 00:13:33,320
What's the point of you going?

241
00:13:38,740 --> 00:13:41,240
(Tianshui Town Inn)

242
00:13:41,240 --> 00:13:41,880
Excuse me.

243
00:13:42,040 --> 00:13:43,480
Have you ever seen someone this tall?

244
00:13:43,680 --> 00:13:45,040
He's a handsome, elegant

245
00:13:45,120 --> 00:13:45,960
and approachable man.

246
00:13:46,240 --> 00:13:47,080
He'll have a woman

247
00:13:47,080 --> 00:13:48,120
about this tall with him.

248
00:13:48,640 --> 00:13:49,280
No.

249
00:13:50,320 --> 00:13:51,160
Alright, thanks.

250
00:13:53,840 --> 00:13:54,400
Miss Qingying.

251
00:13:56,680 --> 00:13:58,080
Were you describing

252
00:13:58,880 --> 00:13:59,680
Chancellor Shen?

253
00:14:00,560 --> 00:14:01,000
Of course.

254
00:14:03,160 --> 00:14:04,240
Handsome,

255
00:14:04,440 --> 00:14:05,520
elegant

256
00:14:06,040 --> 00:14:06,880
and approachable?

257
00:14:10,760 --> 00:14:12,600
It seems we will never find them.

258
00:14:13,080 --> 00:14:13,760
Why?

259
00:14:16,360 --> 00:14:17,200
If you ask me,

260
00:14:17,720 --> 00:14:19,120
Shen Zaiye suffered this misfortune

261
00:14:19,600 --> 00:14:21,600
simply because he has too many enemies.

262
00:14:22,040 --> 00:14:23,040
It's destined.

263
00:14:23,520 --> 00:14:25,500
The evil things he's done
haven't gone unpunished.

264
00:14:25,880 --> 00:14:27,920
They're just waiting for him
to lose power

265
00:14:27,920 --> 00:14:29,240
so that they can rise against him.

266
00:14:29,550 --> 00:14:31,320
You scholars
have studied yourselves stupid.

267
00:14:31,320 --> 00:14:32,880
You can't tell who's good and who's bad.

268
00:14:34,240 --> 00:14:34,680
Sure.

269
00:14:35,120 --> 00:14:36,120
He's a good man.

270
00:14:36,640 --> 00:14:38,480
Why hasn't he shown any concern

271
00:14:38,600 --> 00:14:39,680
for the ladies you rescued?

272
00:14:41,040 --> 00:14:41,480
Miss.

273
00:14:41,720 --> 00:14:42,440
Miss, save me.

274
00:14:42,760 --> 00:14:44,320
There's a bad guy who's been tailing me.

275
00:14:44,320 --> 00:14:45,160
I'm scared.

276
00:14:46,040 --> 00:14:47,040
Miss, save me.

277
00:14:49,440 --> 00:14:49,960
What?

278
00:14:52,160 --> 00:14:53,240
How dare they be this brazen

279
00:14:53,480 --> 00:14:54,200
in broad daylight?

280
00:14:54,200 --> 00:14:55,520
I'll help you teach them a lesson.

281
00:14:55,520 --> 00:14:55,840
Alright.

282
00:14:56,089 --> 00:14:56,480
Qingying.

283
00:15:06,480 --> 00:15:08,540
They're begging on the streets
at such a young age.

284
00:15:12,040 --> 00:15:12,640
Tell me.

