00:28:26,880 --> 00:28:27,880
But you have to remember

577
00:28:28,800 --> 00:28:29,880
not to act rashly

578
00:28:30,480 --> 00:28:32,320
before you're absolutely sure

579
00:28:32,520 --> 00:28:33,880
of what you're doing.

580
00:28:35,320 --> 00:28:37,640
Are you sure
your brother will be released

581
00:28:38,000 --> 00:28:39,560
after you hand us over to the foreman?

582
00:28:42,000 --> 00:28:43,480
But my brother...

583
00:28:43,920 --> 00:28:45,000
Lian, don't worry.

584
00:28:46,240 --> 00:28:47,360
This treacherous chancellor

585
00:28:47,480 --> 00:28:48,800
doesn't do a lot of good deeds,

586
00:28:49,200 --> 00:28:50,000
but this time,

587
00:28:50,560 --> 00:28:52,200
he'll help you rescue your brother.

588
00:28:53,320 --> 00:28:54,040
Really?

589
00:28:56,480 --> 00:28:58,360
If you want to do good deeds,
don't include me.

590
00:28:59,280 --> 00:29:00,040
Betray once,

591
00:29:00,120 --> 00:29:01,440
and you'll never be trusted again.

592
00:29:02,400 --> 00:29:04,120
She failed in harming me this time,

593
00:29:04,280 --> 00:29:05,880
who knows if there won't be a next time?

594
00:29:08,880 --> 00:29:10,000
Everyone makes mistakes.

595
00:29:10,360 --> 00:29:11,640
Let alone a child this young.

596
00:29:13,720 --> 00:29:14,280
Being a child

597
00:29:15,320 --> 00:29:16,880
isn't a reason for her to make mistakes.

598
00:29:27,720 --> 00:29:28,720
You want to protect her?

599
00:29:29,840 --> 00:29:30,240
Yes.

600
00:29:33,120 --> 00:29:33,840
Jiang Taohua.

601
00:29:34,560 --> 00:29:36,040
Don't blame me for not reminding you.

602
00:29:37,280 --> 00:29:38,040
Be careful

603
00:29:38,440 --> 00:29:39,840
not to let her control you someday.

604
00:29:51,640 --> 00:29:52,840
(Shen Zaiye said before)

605
00:29:53,200 --> 00:29:54,600
(that he isn't from a noble family.)

606
00:29:54,770 --> 00:29:56,640
(He has experienced
the ups and downs of life.)

607
00:29:58,880 --> 00:30:00,360
(What has he been through)

608
00:30:01,680 --> 00:30:02,840
(to make him so cautious)

609
00:30:03,880 --> 00:30:05,360
(toward everyone?)

610
00:30:25,600 --> 00:30:26,480
What do we do?

611
00:30:27,080 --> 00:30:27,920
The mark ends here.

612
00:30:30,240 --> 00:30:31,760
There seems to be someone over there.

613
00:30:33,760 --> 00:30:34,120
Let's go.

614
00:30:46,230 --> 00:30:46,640
Granny.

615
00:30:48,240 --> 00:30:48,520
Granny.

616
00:30:48,880 --> 00:30:49,200
Granny.

617
00:30:50,800 --> 00:30:51,360
What's wrong?

618
00:30:51,640 --> 00:30:52,640
Your rice bag is leaking.

619
00:30:53,720 --> 00:30:54,280
Unbelievable.

620
00:30:54,880 --> 00:30:56,040
Thank you, young man.

621
00:30:56,640 --> 00:30:57,840
I was wondering

622
00:30:58,040 --> 00:31:00,200
why the rice bag was getting lighter.

623
00:31:00,480 --> 00:31:01,640
Granny, let me carry it.

624
00:31:02,600 --> 00:31:02,880
Sure.

625
00:31:05,840 --> 00:31:07,080
Young people nowadays

626
00:31:07,840 --> 00:31:09,200
are all kind.

627
00:31:11,840 --> 00:31:12,360
Granny.

628
00:31:12,880 --> 00:31:14,160
When you said all,

629
00:31:14,280 --> 00:31:15,000
have you met

630
00:31:15,040 --> 00:31:16,480
other kind young people?

631
00:31:16,800 --> 00:31:17,400
Yes.

632
00:31:17,640 --> 00:31:18,560
A few days ago,

633
00:31:18,640 --> 00:31:20,080
a couple came to the village.

634
00:31:22,280 --> 00:31:24,840
They're as kind as you and your husband.

635
00:31:24,840 --> 00:31:25,560
- Granny.
- Granny.

636
00:31:25,560 --> 00:31:26,680
- We're not...
- We're not...

637
00:31:29,760 --> 00:31:30,880
- That couple...
- You said...

638
00:31:34,320 --> 00:31:35,440
- That couple...
- You said...

639
00:31:38,800 --> 00:31:39,720
Calm down.

640
00:31:41,240 --> 00:31:42,960
I'll take you to meet

641
00:31:43,040 --> 00:31:43,520
that man

642
00:31:43,880 --> 00:31:44,640
and that lady.

643
00:31:46,520 --> 00:31:46,960
Follow me.

644
00:31:47,000 --> 00:31:47,320
Sure.

645
00:31:47,652 --> 00:31:48,480
My home

646
00:31:48,680 --> 00:31:49,520
is right ahead of us.

647
00:31:54,800 --> 00:31:55,400
Grandma.

648
00:31:56,400 --> 00:31:56,920
Grandma.

649
00:31:56,920 --> 00:31:57,520
I'm home!

650
00:31:57,840 --> 00:31:58,480
You're home.

651
00:31:58,680 --> 00:32:00,400
I went to buy buns with Miss.

652
00:32:00,920 --> 00:32:01,640
Really?

653
00:32:03,200 --> 00:32:04,000
Here, try it.

654
00:32:05,120 --> 00:32:05,560
Sure.

655
00:32:06,560 --> 00:32:07,600
Smells good.

656
00:32:10,080 --> 00:32:10,560
Is it good?

657
00:32:10,840 --> 00:32:11,480
Yes.

658
00:32:13,800 --> 00:32:14,840
Having seen this,

659
00:32:14,880 --> 00:32:16,320
do you still have the heart to kill?

660
00:32:16,480 --> 00:32:17,320
Give me another bite.

661
00:32:21,600 --> 00:32:22,720
Never mind what I think,

662
00:32:23,440 --> 00:32:24,280
your behavior today

663
00:32:25,080 --> 00:32:26,280
is out of the ordinary.

664
00:32:30,800 --> 00:32:32,280
A person focused on protecting herself

665
00:32:32,880 --> 00:32:34,360
is meddling in other people's affairs.

666
00:32:36,200 --> 00:32:37,920
Perhaps it's a trivial matter
for others,

667
00:32:38,720 --> 00:32:39,600
but it means

668
00:32:39,960 --> 00:32:41,080
everything to her.

669
00:32:42,040 --> 00:32:43,520
You ruined her innocence,

670
00:32:44,040 --> 00:32:46,320
and now you blame her for being cunning.

671
00:32:47,880 --> 00:32:49,200
If someone could help her,

672
00:32:49,700 --> 00:32:51,800
she wouldn't have done
such a dangerous thing today.

673
00:32:54,840 --> 00:32:56,980
It's only normal
that someone high and mighty like you

674
00:32:57,480 --> 00:32:59,280
doesn't understand what lowly commoners

675
00:33:00,000 --> 00:33:00,480
suffer.

676
00:33:19,360 --> 00:33:19,880
Six people?

677
00:33:26,200 --> 00:33:26,640
Granny.

678
00:33:26,640 --> 00:33:28,980
Why are there two extra sets
of bowls and chopsticks today?

679
00:33:31,240 --> 00:33:32,040
That's because

680
00:33:32,160 --> 00:33:33,520
the people who came to look for you

681
00:33:33,920 --> 00:33:35,000
have arrived at the village.

682
00:33:36,880 --> 00:33:39,560
So I prepared two more sets
of bowls and chopsticks.

683
00:33:40,560 --> 00:33:42,280
We'll eat together later.

684
00:34:24,200 --> 00:34:24,520
Zaiye.

685
00:34:26,720 --> 00:34:27,480
Qingying?

686
00:34:27,800 --> 00:34:28,280
Your High...

687
00:34:28,280 --> 00:34:28,880
Your Highness.

688
00:34:28,880 --> 00:34:29,480
Mr. Wuxia.

689
00:34:29,960 --> 00:34:30,640
Why are you here?

690
00:34:31,280 --> 00:34:32,920
We followed the marks here.

691
00:34:33,160 --> 00:34:34,480
We also met Granny on the way.

692
00:34:35,400 --> 00:34:36,080
When you two

693
00:34:36,080 --> 00:34:37,440
wear my brother's clothes,

694
00:34:37,600 --> 00:34:39,440
people might mistake you for brothers.

695
00:34:43,480 --> 00:34:44,640
When you say it like that...

696
00:34:56,080 --> 00:34:57,880
They do look similar at first glance.

697
00:35:03,360 --> 00:35:03,760
Of course.

698
00:35:03,760 --> 00:35:04,960
My brother is better looking.

699
00:35:11,400 --> 00:35:13,240
Don't just stand there.

700
00:35:13,440 --> 00:35:14,160
Start cooking.

701
00:35:32,000 --> 00:35:32,520
Thank you.

702
00:35:34,440 --> 00:35:36,280
What happened along the way?

703
00:35:37,120 --> 00:35:38,000
Why did you come here?

704
00:35:38,840 --> 00:35:40,880
I'm fine. Thank you for your concern.

705
00:35:41,960 --> 00:35:42,760
We're friends.

706
00:35:43,080 --> 00:35:44,240
No need to be so polite.

707
00:35:53,320 --> 00:35:54,560
You're so biased.

708
00:35:54,680 --> 00:35:55,600
They're both in danger.

709
00:35:55,610 --> 00:35:57,740
Why do you only care
about Lady Jiang and not Zaiye?

710
00:36:03,960 --> 00:36:05,640
He has always
been shrewd and calculating.

711
00:36:05,820 --> 00:36:07,840
He won't tolerate anyone
taking advantage of him.

712
00:36:08,560 --> 00:36:09,360
I guess

713
00:36:10,180 --> 00:36:11,760
he doesn't need
me to worry about him.

714
00:36:15,800 --> 00:36:17,080
You're good.

715
00:36:18,280 --> 00:36:20,560
You made Mr. Wuxia to pity you.

716
00:36:21,280 --> 00:36:22,160
I'm impressed.

717
00:36:24,920 --> 00:36:26,800
Mr. Wuxia is a man of integrity.

718
00:36:27,280 --> 00:36:28,640
I'm honored

719
00:36:28,840 --> 00:36:29,720
to have your concern.

720
00:36:39,080 --> 00:36:40,440
All he's good at is sweet-talking.

721
00:36:40,550 --> 00:36:42,280
If I hadn't protected him
on our way here,

722
00:36:42,440 --> 00:36:44,280
he wouldn't
even have the chance to pity her.

723
00:36:46,560 --> 00:36:48,360
You're a little reckless sometimes,

724
00:36:49,000 --> 00:36:50,840
but you did help a lot.

725
00:36:51,480 --> 00:36:52,400
Thank you.

726
00:36:57,360 --> 00:36:57,760
Qingying.

727
00:36:58,760 --> 00:37:00,560
Mr. Wuxia is sincerely thanking you,

728
00:37:00,880 --> 00:37:02,200
but you're rude to him.

729
00:37:02,200 --> 00:37:03,280
Why aren't you apologizing?

730
00:37:10,280 --> 00:37:11,360
Are you serious?

731
00:37:11,680 --> 00:37:13,200
Why are you helping an outsider?

732
00:37:13,760 --> 00:37:14,880
I'm rude?

733
00:37:15,280 --> 00:37:17,360
He doesn't seem to be polite to you.

734
00:37:17,720 --> 00:37:18,920
Mr. Wuxia is of noble status.

735
00:37:19,600 --> 00:37:20,680
How can we compare to him?

736
00:37:27,360 --> 00:37:28,840
You're saying I'm being disrespectful.

737
00:37:31,520 --> 00:37:31,800
Fine.

738
00:37:42,360 --> 00:37:43,720
He cares about Lady Jiang.

739
00:37:44,440 --> 00:37:47,040
Splashing water on Lady Jiang
isn't disrespectful, is it?

740
00:37:57,000 --> 00:37:57,640
Qingying.

741
00:37:58,200 --> 00:37:59,520
You can't bully me.

742
00:38:06,000 --> 00:38:07,840
Qingying splashed water on me
because of you.

743
00:38:07,920 --> 00:38:09,280
I'm going to splash you, of course.

744
00:38:09,920 --> 00:38:11,840
It's called giving someone

745
00:38:12,000 --> 00:38:13,160
a taste of their own medicine.

746
00:38:18,440 --> 00:38:19,520
How dare you splash Zaiye?

747
00:38:19,840 --> 00:38:20,480
Just wait.

748
00:38:52,280 --> 00:38:52,800
How immature.

749
00:38:57,640 --> 00:38:58,680
Is he mad?

750
00:39:08,160 --> 00:39:08,600
Granny.

751
00:39:10,440 --> 00:39:10,920
Granny.

752
00:39:11,600 --> 00:39:13,240
Did they argue?

753
00:39:14,720 --> 00:39:15,640
No.

754
00:39:16,080 --> 00:39:17,160
They might

755
00:39:17,160 --> 00:39:19,040
be worried about the village.

756
00:39:20,800 --> 00:39:21,960
What happened to the village?

757
00:39:41,801 --> 00:39:45,091
♪The flower bloomed,
knowing nothing at all♪

758
00:39:45,091 --> 00:39:48,121
♪In splendor, proud and tall♪

759
00:39:49,031 --> 00:39:52,261
♪The flower fell, lashed by the wind♪

760
00:39:52,261 --> 00:39:56,021
♪In a daze,
it felt like lifetimes had thinned♪

761
00:39:56,321 --> 00:39:59,501
♪Petals soaked in rain♪

762
00:39:59,501 --> 00:40:02,841
♪Heartbreak follows again and again♪

763
00:40:03,221 --> 00:40:06,891
♪The flower weeps, burdened by thoughts♪

764
00:40:06,891 --> 00:40:12,611
♪With no one it can be brought♪

765
00:40:17,561 --> 00:40:24,491
♪Wishes struggle through the mire♪

766
00:40:24,901 --> 00:40:31,741
♪Regrets clash in hopeless fire♪

767
00:40:32,251 --> 00:40:39,251
♪Still I hope she'll pick the flower
kissed by dew♪

768
00:40:39,551 --> 00:40:43,701
♪Even if it means this flower♪

769
00:40:43,701 --> 00:40:50,671
♪Will be hers to give to someone new♪

770
00:41:01,801 --> 00:41:05,001
♪Whose eyes
did the flower's heart meet?♪

771
00:41:05,001 --> 00:41:08,251
♪Love and hate held back, discreet♪

772
00:41:08,601 --> 00:41:12,381
♪The flower withers, feelings in decay♪

773
00:41:12,381 --> 00:41:18,961
♪No longer needing to say♪

774
00:41:23,021 --> 00:41:29,961
♪Yet I still long for her in madness♪

775
00:41:30,351 --> 00:41:37,321
♪Unafraid of judgment or sadness♪

776
00:41:37,661 --> 00:41:44,661
♪Remembering the words
she spoke of flowers and skies♪

777
00:41:45,031 --> 00:41:46,801
♪And finding♪

778
00:41:46,801 --> 00:41:55,801
♪They were her gentle heart's reply♪
